<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">

      <h1>Help with ContraDB</h1>

      <dl class=help-faq>
        <dt>Why are we here?</dt> <dd><%= link_to "the ‘About’ page", about_path %></dd>
        <dt>How do I enter a dance?</dt> <dd><a href="https://youtu.be/1NSr-_tx08s" target="_blank">video tutorial</a>, and perhaps <a href="https://github.com/contradb/contra/wiki/Curating-Dances" target="_blank">community guidelines for curating dances</a></dd>
        <dt>How do I search for dances?</dt> <dd><a href="https://github.com/contradb/contra/wiki/Dance-Figure-Filters" target="_">wiki page</a></dd>
        <dt>What is a gentlespoon?</dt> <dd>that's our default dialect. Don't like it? Log in and adjust it using the <%= link_to("dialect editor", dialect_path) %>. There's a ton you do with dialects, see <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ENMyXnJurKc&t=0s" target="_">this video tutorial</a></dd>
        <dt>Can someone talk me through this?</dt> <dd><%= mail_to Rails.application.secrets.admin_help_mail, Rails.application.secrets.admin_help_name, encode: 'hex' %> is happy to help you through using the site</dd>
        <dt>A dance I wrote is mis-entered, my name is misspelled, or I would like my dance taken down.</dt> <dd><%= mail_to Rails.application.secrets.admin_help_mail, Rails.application.secrets.admin_help_name, encode: 'hex' %> keeps our data clean and consensual. Contact her to add information to a choreographer page representing you.</dd>
        <dt>The site has a bug!</dt> <dd><%= mail_to Rails.application.secrets.admin_code_mail, Rails.application.secrets.admin_code_name, encode: 'hex' %> would like to hear about it</dd>
        <dt>what are contradb.com's dance sharing ethics?</dt> <dd>we're currently gathering community input, please <a href="https://github.com/contradb/contra/issues/297">participate</a></dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
